 nowrap><b><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'>Cuku</font></b></td>
        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'> Don't be surprised they are not responding to our class. The Necro population in EQ has been declining since EQ went commercial and they started the necro nerfs in an effeort to stop solo'ers and encourage team play. It used to be that everyone wanted to be a necro because of our power, now not many at all do because of all of our nerfs, and lack of attention paid to the class by VI.</P><P>Back to the original topic tho :)</P><P>They have given us focus items that increase dot DPS (it's extremely poor tho when compared to the other focus items). And as it stands now (hopefully they adding more items) the afflcition ext, haste, effciency 3 focus items are nearly impossible to get. So while the lower level players have tons of items they can get for dot focus effects, those of use using spells over lvl 44, probally wont see the items at all because they mostly on the uber mobs in ToV, with a couple in planes, but then they on items that drop maybe 5% of time.</P><P>The affliction series ( ext, haste, and efficiency) all reduce the mana or cast time of our spells (although the effeciency effect I swear is not fixed but a random effect). Remember we aren't melee so don't think of things in DPS, rather look at it as damage per mana. All of those focus help us reduce the mana or cast time. Ext will do 20% more damage for same mana, Effc will reduce the mana by 20% they say, and haste decreases cast time. If u can somehow get all three items then u doing really well. But, as I mentioned earlier, fat friggen chance that will happen for focus 3 items.</P><P>None of this really helps on raids tho because we really don't do much damage except on the boss mobs where our dots can have full effect. Just resign yorself to the fact as a solo'er nothing can touch us. But when you go on raids, you role is not that of a damage dealer, but a mana battery, group healer, group buffer (when u can land the degen, mindwrack, and crippling spells), back up mezzer at times, and reserve cleric for wipeouts and u need to rez ppl :) It's a very important role, and one I'm glad we can do now, I'm just wish we were more efficient at mana transfer.</P><P>I find it ironic that I am a master of death, untouchable at soloing high end mobs. But when I go on raids, I am more cleric/chanter than anything else.</P><P>On the AA topic (VI didn't take any time at all on BST AA skills, and took only slightly more time on us and Magi) There are 2 skills that are helpful tho. Spell Casting Mastery and the Channeling Focus. Of course SCM only works on our specialized spells, but I'm sure most of us specialized in alteration which is where most of our dots are. So that helps us reduce mana when it works. The channeling ( I'll come back to this one when I get to 50aa points) helps with us to continue casting when getting beat on.</P><P>The magi focused earings also work on our dots now too. They dont do more damage for us, but it does save some mana.</P><P>I for one would like to see VI do some other things for our class rather than work on focus stuff. As solo'ers I have no problem at all with much of anything in our class, but in raids we need some massive help.</P><P>First, I'd like to see a AA ability that allows us to transfer mana alot more effeciently (Maybe they could replace our 59aa ability that let's us turn our GROUP buff into a ae buff, seeing as how we have ZERO group buffs to begin with). The 400 of my mana to 150 for someone else is a joke. Magi upgraded mods rods give 650 mana or so per rod, and takes like 400 mana to cast. We have been transfering mana since low levels you would think we would get better at it by level 60 :) I'd like to see a transfer rate of say 500 mana to 350 as a lvl 59 aa. Much like the SHM 59aa Canni upgraded skill.</P><P>I'd also like to see us get critical dots. There can be no arguement from VI that this will unbalance game play, when wiz can crit for 6k on reg spells, and the best we could crit for with FP would be 4300 and our recast time on dots is a min of 54 secs, so it's not like we will be casting spells as often as wizards or magi.</P><P>Ok, I've ranted enough here :) I'll make a complete post on class suggestions later after I do a bit more research on other classes AA and damage outputs, and raid roles.</P><P>Cuku Keechoo - Iksar Warlock<BR>FV Server - Fire & Fury</P><P><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=223050" target="_blank">http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=223050</a> </P><P></P><P> </font></td>
